+## Three-Layer Checkpoint Architecture
+
+durable-request uses three layers, each reinforcing the next. The agent tries them in order; if a layer succeeds, the lower layers act as safety nets.
+
+```
+Layer 1 (deterministic)     Layer 2 (tool-based)          Layer 3 (conversational)
+─────────────────────────   ────────────────────────────   ────────────────────────
+stop hook                   AskQuestion / AskUserQuestion  Numbered text options
+.cursor/hooks.json          Built-in agent tool            Plain text fallback
+Runs OUTSIDE the LLM        Blocks agent turn, UI widget   Works everywhere
+Auto-continues the loop     User picks from options        User types response
+```
+
+**Layer 1 is installed separately** (see install.md). The agent does not call it — Cursor calls it automatically when the agent's turn ends. Layers 2 and 3 are what the agent controls.
+
